We are seeking a skilled and proactive Testing Specialist to join our team in Brussels, (near-site & freelance contract). The Testing Specialist will primarily focus on preparing and executing technical work related to the testing of applications. This will be performed under the supervision of a Team Leader, and will include preparing detailed testing reports. The role requires close collaboration with the application/project teams, following procedures set by the Contracting Authorities, during the planning and execution of testing campaigns.




Key Responsibilities:

Assisting with evaluation and testing of applications to help ensure that they conform to the Contracting Authority's requirements and methodology, including specification of logical tests cases, execution of test cases, and checking and assessing test results;

Integration testing;

Producing technical documentation;

Assessing the test processes and tools.




Other specific expertise

Good analytical skills;
Capability of integration in an international/multicultural environment, rapid self-starting capability and experience in team working;
Ability to work in an accurate, objective but supportive and service-oriented way;
Capability to be sensitive and positively critical;
Good oral and written communication, in particular for quality and testing result reporting.







